                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.79611 Pan American Airways, Inc./172:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-11T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 11, 1928—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>89. The Department is informed that Pan American Airways, Inc. and W. R. Grace
                    &amp; Company are asking the Chilean Government for a concession for commercial
                    air mail service from Arica south in the name of the Chilean Airways
                    Corporation, an American company, and are submitting definite written
                    proposition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
